hopobject.body: I do some voluntary work anabolicus.com The idea of Diane Abbott influencing anything other than Michael Portillo’s shirt colour would have provoked hollow laughter in Labour Party circles in 2010. But not now. She may not have come close winning the Labour leadership but she has skilfully used her campaign to promote her own agenda and increase her political profile throughout the media. She accepted a front bench position shadowing health and become one of Labour’s best front bench performers. She threatened to resign if Labour were to whip in favour of Syrian intervention, which luckily for her didn’t happen.
